{# Button card #}
<h2>Button card</h2>
{# What #}
<h3>What is it?</h3>
<ul>
    <li>A card with several buttons in.</li>
</ul>
{# When to #}
<h3>When to use it?</h3>
<ul>
    <li>To direct users to different content relevant to their needs.</li>
    <li>At the end of the main page content. We found that users preferred to split lots of content into smaller, specific pages and that this was the best way to continue the journey after reading the main overview content.</li>
</ul>
{# When not to #}
<h3>When not to use it?</h3>
<ul>
    <li>To attract the user's attention if there is no benefit to them reading the content.</li>
    <li>To list links within a section or related content. Use the in-line navigation card instead.</li>
</ul>

{# Set up buttons #}
{% from "wmnds/patterns/content-cards/buttons/_buttons.njk" import wmndsContentCardButtons %}

